Arsenal’s last Europa League group fixture this season, is a trip to Standard Liege. The Gunners go into the game top of Group F with 10 points, while their Belgian hosts are third with seven. Arsenal have all but qualified for the round of 32, but just need to avoid a heavy defeat on Thursday to make sure. Kick off is 6.55pm West African time. Thursday, December 12
